Trade/Device Name(s): N Antisera to Human Immunoglobulins (IgG, IgA, and IgM)
Regulation Name(s): Immunoglobulins A, G, M, D, and E Immunological Test System
Document Summary: FDA 510(k) summary for Siemens N Antisera to Human Immunoglobulins (IgG, IgA, and IgM) in serum, plasma, urine, and CSF by immunonephelometry with added High Dose Hook claim for CSF samples.
Indications for Use Summary: In-vitro diagnostic reagents for quantitative determination of immunoglobulins (IgG, IgA, IgM) in human serum, heparinized and EDTA plasma, and IgG in urine and CSF by immunonephelometry on BN II and BN ProSpec systems; IgG measurement aids in diagnosing abnormal protein metabolism and immune deficiencies.
